{
  "texts": [
    "C. Large Language Model in Data ExplorationLLM-based tools have been proposed for data exploration and visualization tasks.",
    "For visualization generation and recommendations, LLM4Vis [14] and ChartGPT [46] utilize LLMs to choose appropriate visualizations from natural language instructions.",
    "Li et al. [47] evaluate the capability of GPT-3.5 to generate visualization specifications, demonstrating its superiority over previous machine learning-based approaches.",
    "NL2Rigel [48] showcases the LLM's ability to convert instructions into comprehensive data visualizations and tables.",
    "For analytical task translation and automation, Hassan et al. [49] and Data-Copilot [16] concentrate on converting analytical goals and ambiguous queries into actionable data analysis tasks."
  ]
}